T1	Intervention 633 740	Anaesthesia and postoperative analgesia were standardized and the same surgeon performed all the operations
T2	Intervention 526 631	randomly allocated to three groups: intraoperative music, postoperative music and silence (control group)
T3	Intervention 742 928	Stress response was assessed during and after surgery by determining the plasma cortisol and blood glucose levels. Immune function was evaluated by studying immunoglobulin A (IgA) levels
T4	Intervention 930 1063	Patients' postoperative pain, anxiety, blood pressure (BP), heart rate (HR) and oxygen saturation were also studied as stress markers
